= August 2012

The goal of all pro-independence parties is to celebrate a binding referendum on independence. How to get there, though, is a complex topic. Basque Ledakhari <span style='color: #1d813c'>Ibarretxe</span> failed to convince the Spanish Congreso in 2008 to allow such referendum for the Basque country, even if more limited in scope. Can the Spanish government be convinced now? Or is it a non-agreement referendum the only way forward?

